  "translations": {
    "en": "As for the right of your master who freed you, know he spent his property for you, brought you from bondage's abasement to freedom's honour, freed you from captivity, loosened slavery's bonds, gave you ownership of yourself, and freed you for worship. Know he is closest to you in life and death, and helping him is incumbent. There is no strength save in Allah. As for the right of the slave you freed, know that Allah made your freeing him a means to Him and veil against the Fire. Your immediate reward is inheriting from him if he has no family, and your ultimate reward is Paradise.",
